description:
Smart West End hotel, steps from Trafalgar Square

Prime location
The elegant Club Quarters, Trafalgar Square is in a historic Victorian building, a stone’s throw from Nelson’s Column monument and Charing Cross Tube Station. You'll be just a few minutes' walk from the National Gallery and National Portrait Gallery.

Iconic landmarks
This vibrant West End location is great for restaurants and theaters, and you’ll be a half-mile from both Big Ben and Piccadilly Circus. For a change of pace, take a 20-minute stroll to St James’s Park.

Thoughtful touches
Free WiFi throughout the hotel and purified bottled water are popular with guests, who also value the helpful staff. There’s an English brasserie and Japanese restaurant on site – or you can take advantage of 24-hour room service.

Home from home
Comfortable guestrooms offer luxury linens, LCD TVs with on-demand movies, and iPod docking stations. Want a refrigerator and microwave in your room? All you have to do is ask.

HOTEL_AMENITY.value:
Dining options at the hotel include a restaurant. A bar/lounge is on site where guests can unwind with a drink. This 4-star property offers access to a business center and a meeting/conference room.

Public areas are equipped with complimentary high-speed wireless Internet access. This London hotel also offers a health club, multilingual staff, and coffee/tea in the lobby.

DINING.value:
Boyds Bar and Brasserie - This brasserie serves breakfast, lunch, and dinner. Guests can enjoy drinks at the bar.

Watatsumi - This fine-dining restaurant serves lunch and dinner. Guests can enjoy drinks at the bar.

Room service (during limited hours) is available.

RECREATION.value: Recreational amenities at the hotel include a health club and a fitness facility.

GOLD.value: Housed in a historic London building, London’s Club Quarters, Trafalgar Square delivers a central location for visiting the top tourist spots. Among free perks are purified bottled water and WiFi throughout. The National Gallery and National Portrait Gallery are a short walk away, and Big Ben and Piccadilly Circus are both within a half-mile.

GUESTS_LOVE.value:
Guests Love
  • Unbeatable central location

  • Helpful staff

  • Clean, comfortable rooms

  • Free WiFi

    • Keep in Mind
  • Some rooms small, but not by London standards

  • Room temperatures may fluctuate

  • Some would have preferred a bathtub rather than a shower

END_OF_THE_DAY.value:
At the end of the day…
Our guests love Club Quarters, Trafalgar Square for its prime West End location, helpful staff, and clean rooms. They also appreciate the free WiFi, though some find guestrooms a bit small and miss having a bathtub.

ROOM_FEATURE.value: When you stay at Club Quarters, Trafalgar Square, you'll be in a fantastic location, just a 5-minute walk from Trafalgar Square and Nelson's Column. Guests can visit the 24-hour health club for a workout or grab a bite to eat at Boyds Bar and Brasserie, which serves British cuisine and is open for breakfast, lunch, and dinner. Rooms at this upscale hotel offer up nice touches like iPod docks and premium bedding, along with 24-hour room service and flat-screen TVs.
